<font class="post">
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>Note: This is old Dane History, I dug it out from our former members board, both to preserve it and to have it available here for the reference. All that have something to say, feel free to reply, but if you do please stay *in character*.<br><br>Desperate put in some exceptional storywriting here...make a huuge cup of coffee and enjoy! ;o)   -Druuni<br>----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 04:34AM <br><br><br>~A crash loud enough to wake up the Lord and Lady of Antonica echoed through the silent halls of Dane Manor as Desperate crashed his axe down on and through the desk in his office. He had never been so enraged, his blood boiled, his one eye floated in adrenaline, locking on another target. A bookshelf. Another crash as the pages of history and legends that graced his office flew from the force of his axe.~<br><br>"What am I doing now? What is Dane." ~The warrior's giant foot crashed through the window knocking out the glass.~ "Damn you Rhyden why did you make me do that?" ~Spittle flew from his lips as he crused. Grabbing a log of past Dane events and chucking it through the now permenantly opened window~ "Who else?" ~The words were comming out with such emotion they would have been hard to understand had he directed the question to anyone other then himself.~ "Who else is gone? Leaving."<br><br>~Dropping a shoulder Desperate charged through his opened door, giving up complete control to the rage that burned inside. The wood splintered and then exploded into the hallway. A shard from the door slid under his armor and pierced his shoulder. His mind was unaware of the hinderance, but his body wasn't. Swinging the axe now with one hand, its razor's edge crashed into the stone wall with a brilliant display of sparks that were only reflections of the turmoil inside him.~<br><br>~His heavey boots clanked off the marble floor of the once great hall.~ "Tribunal? Are you looking down?" ~The axe crashed through the door of Desperate's personal quarters. Releasing the grip, he left the axe hanging. Shedding his armor was always a task, but in his current state, his fingers fumbled, his feet tangled and his body seemed uncooperative. Falling to the ground, Desperate ripped his breastplate from his chest and threw it against the wall, leaving a large dent in the armor and a chip in the wall.~<br><br>~The crashing of armor and cursing continued until Desperate was dressed in his kilt and war paint. In the cornor of his room, in front of his window was an alter. Where he had prayed many a night for guidence to his gods. Incense, some herbs, a few small candles and a dagger sat on it. Like a bolt from a wizards's palm, the warrior's hand shot down grabbing the dagger.~ "You forsake me? You forsake my family? I forsake you." <br><br>~Desperate made one final sacrifice to the tribunal, asking for not, offering only his hatred, the dagger slid acrossed his opened palm with a single smooth motion. Blood poured over the alter. Muttering a chant in his native language he had learned in ages past, Desperate drug the dagger over his bear chest. Then slammed the tip of the bloodied dagger into the alter with such might that the stone table accepted it. The blood from the dagger gave the illusion that it was the alter that was bleeding.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br> Anger destroys everything until it is all that is left <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 04:52AM <br><br><br>~The rampage continued. The other members of Dane were either leaving the Manor to Desperate's tirate, or no one was here. His feet slapped bear against the marble now as he made his way to the great hall. The Hall of Dane. The hall he himself restored when all seemed lost.~<br><br>~Comming to Fuduce's picture first. Desperate looked over the portrait.~ "When I first took my place as Sylverdane's successor, you professed your loyality to Dane. You bade me not to forget your pressence even though it was afar. And I didn't. I saved your chair at the table." ~Desperate's hand motioned behind him and towards the officer's hall~ "And still you left." ~Desperate reached up and grabbed the huge framed slamming it into the ground.~<br><br>~Rollo's hung next. Shaking his head Desperate looked over it as well~ "You are like a ghost. Gone from out halls too much." ~Desperate pulled down this portrait as well.~<br><br>~Starweaver stood proudly next on the wall.~ "I once hailed you as a god. I must have seemed like a child in your eyes. But how long has it been since you casted those eyes to Dane?" ~Desperate pulled down the painted and tossed it in a pile with the others.~<br><br>~Larger then the rest, as in life hung Rudra. Desperate stood under his gaze for a moment. Looking up at his long time friend. Finally his words came out thick, Desperate was choking on them.~ "General Rudra. You once encumpassed what it ment to be Dane. You once stood as a measurment for all Danes to be compared. But now? As our walls fall? As our members fight each other? Now where do you stand?" ~Ripping down Rudra's likeness, Desperate brought it to the pile and slammed it down atop the rest.~<br><br>~Dia came down next, then Kvyn, Rhyden, Pepie. The pile grew higher in the great hall, and the walls grew barer. Myssi, Dreamwork, Secil, until finally every portrait from the Hall of Danes lay in one giant pile. With a groan and alot of strain Desperate lifted all of the portraits from the ground and carried them into the Officer's hall.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Anger destroys everything until it is all that is left <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 05:12AM <br><br><br>~In the center of the room was a large granite table, surrounded by plush chairs. A few torches were always lit under the portraits of the Danes. Not Dane as in Hand of Dane, but Dane as in, Stonedane, Riverdane, Thunderrdane, Wynddane, Hipdane, Fyredane, Cleverdane, Hippidane, Lleudane, the people who wandered Norrath forever carrying the name and the spirit of Dane. Taking up the entire north wall was Sylverdane, standing next to Emaus, watching everything.~<br><br>~Desperate threw the portraits he was carrying on the center of the table. He walked behind the head chair, and pulled a bottle of firewater and a cigar from a cabinet. Sylerdane's eyes watched over everything. Desperate refused to look at his portrait, but could feel it staring at him. Desperate lit his cigar, and flicked the matches on the paintings. The table now held one of the largest bon-fires Desperate had ever seen. The heat seemed to have a soul, it pushed back at the warrior and the walls of the hall.~<br><br>~Desperate refused to give an inch to the fire. The heat from its blaze filled the room. Finally Desperate turned towards Sylverdane and raised the bottle, took a large gulp and threw it on the now inferno that blazed behind him. Desperate's eye met Sylver's. The flickering from the flames gave life to the painting. It seemed contorted under the dancing light with the same anger that burned inside of Desperate.~<br><br>"I realized somthing today Sylver. It took me a long while, but I finally realized." ~Desperate chuckled briefly~ "You obviously didn't choose me because I was quick of thought. But eventually the thought does get through my thick skull."<br><br>"With everyday that passes, Hand of Dane sinks further out of control. The name means less and less. I don't know half of our members any longer. And I don't believe they know you. Or what it means to hold your name. They think they are a new breed. They believe that the elders don't know what it is like anymore. And our ways are like that of the Dragon's, words that only discribe myth. And every time that Hand of Dane gets scoffed at, those with the name Dane are scoffed at as well."<br><br>~Desperate fell backwards, the fire singed his back. His head swam and his mind blurred. He pulled himself up and stepped under the portrait.~<br><br>"I tried. But I realized that I failed you." ~Desperate reached up and rested his hands on the base of the painting.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br>User Options:  Edit Message <br> <br>      Druuni<br>Posted On 06/26/01 06:33AM <br><br><br>One word slips to my mind....<br><br>(= Druuni, stubborn elven officer of Dane! *<br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      Wynddane<br>Posted On 06/26/01 12:06PM <br><br><br>:::The Cleric watches a friend....an old friend....a friend that has been his from the moment he stepped onto Norrath go into a frenzied rage....he has never seen him likw this before.....Lost.....Confused....he watched Desperate rip down most of the pictures of the officers he chose....watched him move into the throne room where sylver once sat and ruled over Dane. There isn't much he can do but he feels as the Priest and Advisor to Dane he must say something....Desperate does not even realize he is there....he walks up behind the fallen warrior and simply whispers to him:::<br><br>"Desperate old friend....The only time we will truly Fail...is the time we start believeing we have already done so.....there are people in the halls that believ in you still.....always will......no matter what old friend remmeber this.....I belive in you......and i always will....even if we are the last 2 standing with the tags...from beginnning to end....Birth to Death...we are Danes.....WE are family.....and you And i have each other....Rest old friend...tommorow is a new day...and we'll find out what it brings.....Together"<br><br><br>Wynddane Soulcleanser<br>Cleric of Marr<br>45th Season<br>Priest and Advisor to the Hand of Dane <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      mrbreeze6<br>Posted On 06/26/01 05:21PM <br><br><br>*walks in to desperates room with his pipe lit, and lets out a ring of smoke as puffs and looks at desperate*<br><br>"you know i have returned to norrath?, and since my return i have been tempted by danes *fallen* brethren rhyden, and kvyn to join thier guild.... BUT rest assured that i stay with dane, and i stand by my oath to be with dane till the end."<br><br>*raises his eyeborw at desperate*<br>"you know you need a smoke, from my pipe the special blend will relax your mind and help you to think clearly"<br><br>*offers his pipe to desperate*<br><br><br>OOC: ive been on for past couple days ive been trying to find you and druuni so we could talk bussness buthavnt seen you guys around when ive been on... any way ill be looking for you.<br><br><br><br>solux mindwarp<br>34th enchanter<br>2 years rallos zek<br>hand of dane<br>NO LONGER MIA! <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 06:01PM <br><br><br>~Desperate sat at the base of Sylverdane's painting for who knew how long. His emotions still so bright burning out of control inside. Wynddane was able to approach him without his realization. When his long time friend and advisor finally spoke Desperate flung into action startled.~<br><br>~Spinning around Desperate reached for his axe, forgetting it still hung in his doorway. His eyes locked on Wynddane's a moment too late as a clenched fist slammed into the side of his brother's head. Desperate tried to pull back the ill-fated punch but to no avail. He recoiled as Wynddane stumbled back a few steps.~<br><br>"I...Wynd.." ~The words refused to leave his lips whatever they would have been. The fury built inside from the fall of an empire exploded once again as Desperate ripped the chair from the ground that stood at the head of the table. Sylverdane had sat there, then Myssi, then reserved for Fuduce and finally himself. With all the strength he could muster the warrior heaved the chair. It sailed over the still blazing inferno and exploded into the wall on the far side of the great hall.~<br><br>~Desperate's hand still bleed from the sacrificial dagger, as he clenched his fist pain seered up his arm and clouded his mind. Once, twice, three times Desperate slammed his bloodied fist into the table, staining the end red with his blood. Blood that he had spilled along side so many great men and women. So many brother's and sisters, friends and family.~<br><br>"Brother!" ~Desperate's eye met Wynddane's bewildered gaze.~ "You silently sit, clensing the souls in the City of Myst. Have you been blinded by the dirt that has clung to our souls here at home? You house falls around you, and you say you are content." ~Desperate's hand flung towards the portrait of Sylverdane and his wife, blood arched painting over the picture as he pointed.~ "Your brother started this Guild, he turned it into a Family. And now it is not the name of the guild that is mocked. It is your name. It is his name." ~Desperate spit out the last few words. The body pait that covered his chest and face was mixing with his wounds. His shoulder, his chest, his hand, the paint's toxins were designed to heighten the berserker rage.~ "And you are content."<br><br>~Crossing the room Desperate flip the blazing paintings off the table and onto the floor. Wynddane seemed stunned either by the blow Desperate had dilevered, the harsh words that flew from his mouth like poison from Necromancer's spell. Or all of the above, the fire, the ruined halls, the anger. Still crossing the hall to the far wall Desperate continued his tyrate.~<br><br>"Tell me brother, what do you see when you look around? Who's faces? Who's names?" ~Desperate spun quickly to face Wynddane from halfway acrossed the room~ "Do you know the people you call brother's and sister's any longer? What is Dane now?"<br><br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 06:07PM <br><br><br>~Unaware of when Solux had entered the hall, or what his presence met, Desperate looked over his returned brother. It did his heart good to see him, but the anger still burned brighter then any light that remained lit in the Manor.~<br><br>"Solux, you and I have crossed words on more then one occassion, if you want your return celebrated as a happy one, don't bring it here."<br><br>~Standing dripping with sweat and blood, halfway between Wynd and Solux the warrior stood both as a man who had just fought a terrible battle, and a man ready to wage war on the world.~<br><br>~Turning his attention from Solux back to Wynddane, Desperate found his tongue once more.~ "Where are your brother's now? Where is Sylver, River, Thunderr, Stone, Fyre, Hip, Hippy, Lleu, Clever, Pagan? Make a plavar with your family. Talk and decide what you want done with your name." <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      Wynddane<br>Posted On 06/26/01 06:48PM <br><br><br>:::Wynddame stands in the room halfway down the hall he sees Desperate 