darkness surrounded the light. He recogonized this place, and the voice from his dreams.~ "I've forsaken you, leave me be." ~Desperate's voice was weary, exhausted.~<br><br>"Forsaken? What does that mean exactly?"<br><br>"I NO LONGER WORSHIP YOU. NO LEAVE ME!" ~Desperate found some bass in his voice as he shouted.~<br><br>"You no longer worship me?" ~The voice laughed. In the music of laughter can be found birds and children, song by instrument and voice, but in this laughter was a blended mix of anger, dispare, apathay, and hatred. Desperate's skin crawled~<br><br>"I've never worshiped you, and I still talk with you."<br><br>~Desperate pushed against the floor, climing the air to his feet. He tried to establish where the voice was comming from so he could look the darkness in the eye.~ "As is your problem. You never shut up, and you never listen."<br><br>~Silence~<br><br>~Desperate reached a hand into the darkness and it vanished at the elbow. He withdrew it whole. The darkness and the silence grew weight, weight that leaned down on Desperate from above. He suddenly felt like he was about to be crushed from somthing from above. Refusing to look up the warrior continued his tyrate.~<br><br>"Too many people are saying the guild is over. The family is saying the end is here. They fight and bicker, they stab each other in the back. They turn cold to their brothers and sister's requests. Everyone tells me the cost is too high. They give and give to the family and yet not one will look around and see what they have in each other."<br><br>~Silence. Rushing doom from above.~<br><br>"I can't make them help each other. I can't make them build the manor they tore down. They yell, but they don't listen. The family is too small, the family is too big. Recruit, close the doors, remove this person bring in that person. Attack this guild, sacrifice to that one. Come help me, leave me alone."<br><br>~The feeling was growing inside, rushing doom from above, a tidal wave, a meteor falling. Somthing, somthing huge about to crash down.~<br><br>~Silence~<br><br>"Have you nothing to say now?" ~Desperate swirled in the light looking on all sides for the voice. Through the silence, through the darkness. It was almost atop him now.~<br><br>"With everyone who leaves, someone follows. Every example that is set, someone believes. Anything that is done or not done drives them away."<br><br>~Desperate closed his eyes. Refusing to wait for the oncomming assult from above. He could feel it like a fire now. Burning, hotter then the lavastorm mountains. Desperate stepped into the darkness out of the light. Vanishing to even himself.~<br><br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: What Gives <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/26/01 09:45PM <br><br><br>~CRACK~<br><br>~Half the table stood propped under Desperate's grap. He tilted it trying to flip it over when the center snapped. Somthing gave.~<br><br>~Like a ruberband pulled to tight the table snapped. Half of it landing on the pile of burning portraits, the other half in Desperate's hands. The weight was now undistributed. Resting soley against the Warrior. He staggered a step, his knee buckled and he collapsed under it's weight.~<br><br>~The brunt of the table slammed into his chest with a crash that echoed through the manor. The warrior laid silent unmoving.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      Topasere<br>Posted On 06/27/01 03:32AM <br><br><br>:: Perched on the windowsill Topa smirks looking at the granite table on top of his unconcious brother. Topa mumbled "Hey bro Granite is hard." Not quite as furious as his brother the rogue was still