d clear his mind. Diadane stood over him screaming somthing. Solux sat smoking a pipe as though all the answers rested in the swirling smoke it emmited. He could sence others, though he couldn't see them.~<br><br>~Desperate's one eye floated around the room. Unable to focus on any one thing, so instead danced over everything. Every breath he took hurt down deep inside, though he couldn't figure out why. When he looked down his bared chest, a gash, his war paint and a huge bruise swirled in an indisernable but deliberate pattern.~<br><br>~Crack~<br><br>~Desperate's ears were ringing. They world had been put on mute. Desperate brought his hands over his ears, the ringing grew louder. The world swam out of focus, and the barbarian fell to his knees. He screamed. The heal spell casted by the paladin had helped his body, but his mind was left realing. His scream seemed to go on forever. He couldn't hear it. Only that terrible ringing.~<br><br>~It is said when your ears ring, someone is talking about you. It occured that everyone must be talking about thier guild leader. Memories of the destruction of his room flashed in his mind. Every portrait torn from the wall. The fire, the axe, Wynddane, Rhyden.~<br><br>"He's lost it...."<br>..."Completely off his rocker..."<br>..."He's never been all there..."<br>..."crazy"...<br>..."crazy"...<br>..."crazy"...<br><br>"I'm not crazy!" ~Desperate muttered. Though who it was directed to was unknown. Obviously to Dia as well. The palidin put his face inches from Desperate's.<br><br>"WHAT?" ~Dia yelled~<br><br>"lost it..." ~Desperate trailed off~<br><br>"DON'T WORRY WE'LL FIND IT!" ~Dia responded looking confused. Still screaming, apparently to make up for the lack of volume that Desperate used. To those around him Dia shouted, "Don't just stand there, Desperate's lost it. Look, help him find it." ~The half-elf shruged to tell the other's he had no clue what either Desperate or himself was talking about.~<br><br