ts Errant has ironed out their problems and is Doing better--<br>--Basylysk has left the guild--<br>--Topasere started a bar fight in High Pass--<br><br>~Desperate's head already begun to pound once again as he read the latest news. He was not looking forward to the conversation that he would have to have with Kvyn. Or Wynddane. He could feel his brother's presence, reading over his shoulder no doubt. He thought he heard an unmistakable laughter of pride when he read his name. He had been following the goings on with Knights Errant ever since his daughter joined thier ranks.~<br><br>~Scribbling quickly Desperate sent word back with Lleudane and set up a meeting with several people at the earliest convience~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: The battle continues <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/27/01 05:17PM <br><br><br>~The first meeting was set for that night. Desperate's office had been put together with haste. It still lay in shambles. He was dressed in full cloth. Taking a break from his endless training. That and he needed to repair his armor.~<br><br>~When Kvyn entered Desperate's office he paid no notice to the destruction in the office.~<br><br>"We need to talk brother." ~Desperate said, getting straight to the point. Kvyn was never one for dancing around the subject.~<br><br>"Long time no see old friend." ~Kvyn let his eyes drift briefly around the office~<br><br>"I'm sure you've heard from Rhyden's departure from the family."<br><br>~Kvyn only nodded~<br><br>"I'm further assuming you heard of Lisandra's removal due to the actions on Rhyden's part?"<br><br>"Blah, blah, blah. Yeah somthing like that." ~Kvyn briefly reminded Desperate of Salamandar. A man who has a commanding presence, and demands authority. And yet has an almost utter distaste for authority. It was a unique blend.~<br><