l wrong, but not deliberatly.~ "When you attack Dane you insult alot of people. And by recruiting from within our ranks that is an attack."<br><br>"Well you removed me. Without knowing everything. Without talking to me. You just kicked me." ~Rhyden was getting to the problem. Desperate challanging him apparently hit Rhyden like a physical assult. Desperate wanted to say it was one of the hardest things he had done. But he couldn't. This had to be resolved.~<br><br>"BULLSHYT! You self removed." ~In truth Desperate was glad he had. Action needed to be taken towards Rhyden, and Desperate wasn't sure if he could remove his long time friend.~<br><br>"Because you told me to." ~Desperate wondered if Rhyden really believed Desperate wanted him out. It was just somthing that had to be done. A sacrifice for the family. Like so many before it.~<br><br>"Wrong. After you threatened Agressor I told you that You should be removed for that." Not that I was going to." ~In truth Desperate didn't know if he could have removed his friend.~<br><br>"Lisan..." ~Rhyden didn't even finish her name before Desperate knew where he was going.~<br><br>"I removed Lisandra because you were going to use her to kill a Black Claw. I'm not getting into this shyt again." ~Desperate's furry flared again.~<br><br>"I was sitting down talking to Salamandar when you removed her without a word."<br><br>"You said the only reason you were getting her was to kill a Black Claw. I couldn't stop you. But I could stop a Dane from attacking a Claw."<br><br>~Desperate took a deep breath. He swallowed his anger. This was not the place for it. Not the place for blame. Not the place for Anger. This was a place to end things~<br><br>~Desperate Continued~ "Rhyden I don't trust you. I dont' trust your priorities, I dont' trust your loyalities. I don't know what you are going to do any more. I want you to stay away from Dane. Let whatever happens happen."<br><br>~The arguement took as large a toll on Rhyden as it had on Desperate. The two men only stared at each other in silence. It could have gone either way. They were either on the brink of an understanding or a battle. The waves hit the rocks and either return to the sea, or break down the mountain.~<br><br>~Rhyden nodded.~<br><br>~Desperate turned. He still had alot to do. And would have more. There was always more to do.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Old Friends Passed <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 06/28/01 12:42PM <br><br><br>~Desdmona sits in her comfortable room she and her husband Aerimus have taken. When there is a pounding at the door...."LET ME IN I SAY... I have urgent business to discuss with you!" Looking around she retrieves her picks to let this person in. A look of anger flashes as she remembers she hasnt the skill to open the door. Agnrily she shakes Aerimus. "Wake Up !! Someone has come to our door demanding to see me......open the door so I might know of his messages." <br>~ Aerimus growls....."What another message from your fallen guild??"<br>~ Desdmona glares at him. "Dont you ever speak of them like that again!!" *Thinking she might actually fight with her mate over this.* " We have had this discussion before. Desperate is my adopted father and I will not have you speak ill of him nor my family. I left them to cleave to you as it should be because we are married. They are still part of me and will be as long as I breathe!"<br>~ Shaking she allows the messenger to deliver his news. It is brief and he reads it quickly studdering....... "Your uhhh your umm...... Desperate has fallen mad. He has destroyed the Halls of Dane. There is talk of the family replacing him. Rhyden has left and many changes have taken place since you went out questing."<br>~ Desdmona snatches the message from him and shoves him out the door. Tearfull, looking at 