 causing problem in my marriage as I am torn between the two men I love and respect the most. Aerimus isnt unfeeling, he knows of the situation. He has his own duties to his family and constantly reminds me of mine. I exist in torment. I aid my new family and long to aid my Danes too.<br>I can only offer you my words and what I have learned. it is up to you, Father to lead them back. To demonstrate that the true path to glory isnt items or experience, but kinship and honor. I cant tell you how to do this, as it was a hard lesson for me to learn myself.<br>~ Laying her head on Desperate's shoulder she looks at the man who took her as his own against all conflicts of race and hatered. <br>~With tears in her eyes she vows she will stand beside him come what may.<br>Choking Desdmona wispers, " I Love You Father, I always will. We will survive this. I do not know if Dane will, but you, me and Topa will pick up what pieces we need to and go on......as always."<br><br>Desdmona Shadowborn<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>Message Edited on 06/28/01 01:36PM by Desdmona  <br>  <br><br> RE: Healing Wounds <br><br> <br>      Grimance<br>Posted On 06/28/01 03:19PM <br><br><br>**grimance sits in silence inside Dane Manor.**<br>**Just listening for the right moment**<br><br>Desperate bleeds, I bleed.<br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> An Idea <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/28/01 03:56PM <br><br><br>~Desperate sat in Greater Faydark, silently listneing to Desdmona. The bottle remained undrank in his hands as she spoke to him. The path she had choosen lead her out the door of the manor, and to her husband. Her visits were rare nowadays, though casually she and Desperate spoke often. He wanted to chuckle when she said she heard he had gone mad. You make one little fire and everyone's ready to commit you.~<br><br>~Finally taking a long pull from northern brew she had given him Desperate let it wash his mind. Moving his eye to her