....not hunting .....not talking....he just looks as if he is staring into nothingness. He has heard rumors of Hand of Dane calling him a traitor because he felt Desperate was not mentally compitent to run Dane anymore.He never denied that....he never sent a message saying it was false...but what they didn't realize was he was acting for the good of Dane. Rumors spread that after Desperate struck Wynddane for the 1st time since they have known each other in Norrath he hasnt been the same.....and they were right....he was not. Desperate and Wynddane had their shaky background...not always seeing eye to eye...But never has it come to blows. Wynddane was cut by this....deeply.He wandered for a while ...some say they saw him in CoM....Unrest....Befallen.....but alas he sits on the docks in Firiona Vie in Kunark.Not saying a word to anyone....just sitting and waiting......Knowing....he utters a few lines:::<br><br>"I did what i thought was right. i do not regret what i have done or said....you want to find me....you'll find me...but i tell you this......"<br><br><br>"..........."<br><br><br><br>".........."<br><br><br>" you might not like what you find"<br><br><br><br><br><br>Wynddane Soulcleanser<br>Cleric of Marr<br>45th Season<br>Priest and Advisor to the Hand of Dane <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Anger destroys everything until it is all that is left <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/29/01 03:33AM <br><br><br>~Desperate walked aimlessly through Faydwer. His heavey steps crossed the small continent and when his eye finally glanced up to see where he was. The warrior stood at the docks in Butcherblocks Mountains. To his left the shuttle to Kunark, to his right the ship that would take him to Freeport.~<br><br>~Left, right, left right, Kunark, Antonica, Fironia Vie, Freeport, left right. Desperate had no clue where he had been going or how long he had been wandering.~<br><br>"Not all who wander are lost" ~Desperate found himself muttering a verse his brother was found of saying. The warrior wondered, had he not looked up here where he would have found himself. His mind was so flooded with thoughts, abstract and broken that it was hard to focus on any one thing. So much had gone wrong over the past few months and not much had gone right. He kept seeing the same faces in the Dane manor, and those were not the ones he was upset with. It was the ones that left, the ones that never went. Where was he going? Desperate silently recited a verse he had learned in his childhood in Everfrost from the wolves.~<br><br>On the road that I have taken,<br>one day, walking, I awaken,<br>amazed to see where I have come,<br>where I'm going, and where I'm from.<br><br>This is not the path I thought.<br>This is not the place I sought.<br>This is not the dream I bought,<br>just a fever of fate I've caught.<br><br>I'll change Highways in a while,<br>at the crossroads, one more mile.<br>My path is lit by my own fire.<br>i'm going only where I desire.<br><br>On the road that I have taken,<br>one day, walking, I awaken.<br>One day, walking I awaken,<br>on the road that I have taken.<br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> Crossroads <br><br> <br>      Lluedane<br>Posted On 06/29/01 03:49AM <br><br><br>::In the shadows walking slowly behind the bewildered leader of Hand of Dane a bard whistled a silent song. Follong him in the concealment of his musical notes.:: Where in the hell was Desperate going? I've been following him for hours. Up one hill down another, through the lake, and around a cornor. ::Questions flashed through Lleu's mind. He had been following his leader since he left the Manor. Things were definatly not right. So lost in his own thoughts the bard almost tripped over Desperate at the docks in Butchblock.:: Now what? ::Desperate just stood there, looking from left to right muttering about being lost to himself.:: This was accomplishing nothing. ::Lleu listened to the verse Desperate recited and made his presence noted.::<br><br>On the road that I have taken,<br>one day, walking, I awaken,<br>amazed to se where I have come,<br>where I'm going, and where I'm from.<br><br>This is not the path I thought.<br>This is not the place I sought.<br>This is not hte dream I bought,<br>just a fever of fate I've caught.<br><br>I'll change Highways in a while,<br>at the crossroads, one more mile.<br>My path is lit by my own fire.<br>I'm going only wher eI desire.<br><br>On the road that I have taken,<br>one day, walking, I awaken.<br>One day, walking, I awaken,<br>on the road that I have taken.<br><br>"No actually wer are standing at the docks." ::The barbarian, a race not exactly known for its intelligence. After all Everfrost had no roads. Even the stupid ogres knew how to make roads, anyway, the barbarian looked confused by Llue's comment. Speaking exageratedly slow Llue tried to explain:: "These are the bucherblock docks. The crossroads are behind us." ::Llue turned and pointed down the road.::<br><br>::Desperate shook his head no:: "Yes, the crossroads are behind us." ::Lluedane shook his head yes.::<br><br>"That isn't what I mean. It is an old poem. I figured a bard to know a thing about hat." ::Desperate said obviously growing irritated by the conversation.::<br><br>"The book of counted sorrows? No, what's that." ::The bard mocked in return.::<br><br>"We can still embrace love,<br>it's not too late.<br>So why do we instead,<br>sleep with hate?<br><br>Belief requires no suspension,<br>to see that hell is our invention,<br>we make hell real,<br>we stroke its fires,<br>and in its flames,<br>our hope expires." <br> <br>   
