RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/29/01 04:04AM <br><br><br>~Llue, the youngest of all Danes, Well him and his brother Pagan, always got on Desperate's nerves quick. He was much like the prince born at the height of an empire. A silver spoon in his mouth with no sence of reality. Desperate had thought on more then one occassion of beating responsibility into the bard with that perverbial spoon. But this time somthing he had said actually made sence. The bard made vague refferences to poems and tails but Desperate turned him off. Focusing instead on what he had said.~<br><br>"The crossroads are behind us." ~I'll change highways in a while, at the crossroads, one more mile. The answer he was seeking. Burried in the verse.~<br><br>~Lleu was reciting somthing else when Desperate cut him off, his voice sharp as a razor.~ "Llue shut up for a minute." ~The bard obeyed. Though more out of shock then obediance.~ "Gather all the Danes you can find. Have them meet at the Butcherblock Crossroads. I'll wait for them there. I want all Danes there."<br><br>"You want me to talk to EVERY dane?" ~Llue's sarcasm was apparent even before he finished.~ "You mean all 5 of us?" ~Had desperate seen a spoon he would have seen what Llue really looked with a spoon in his mouth, or down his throat.~ "That could take an hour!"<br><br>"Llue so help me, you spoiled little shyt. If you don't I'll let Topasere loose on you." ~Topasere was not half as diplomatic as his brother and had no difficulties fufilling any thought that crossed his mind. Needless to say the two didn't get along.~ "I want you to invite all Danes. Past and present. We will decide what is to be done now.<br><br>~Llue silently nodded and boarded the ship to Freeport.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/29/01 04:31AM <br><br><br>((OOC:))Slipping out of character for a moment let me first say. Thank you to everyone who has participated in his story line. The work here has been excellent. Just like the characters in a book you've all shown somthing about your characters and yourselves.<br><br>Grimance's patience and steadfast loyality to me and to Dane.<br><br>Solux tokin' on his pipe like Bilbo Baggins.<br><br>Topasere's sometimes dark humor, and rogueish manner.<br><br>Desdmona's split between the two guilds<br><br>Wynddane's and my rocky past and our supsequent personality change overs.<br><br>Dia's ...uh....psychotic behavior. And yes he's always like that<br><br>The problems between Rhyden and I<br><br>Kvyn's easy acceptance of everything. He's always struck me as a guy you could tell anything to and he would only nod and continue unfazed with life. "Huge 3 headed Aliens just landed in my back yard." -- "Uh huh, damn I need a beer."<br><br>When you participate in a story line, even slightly you let people get to know you who otherwise wouldn't get the chance. Either because of different time's on-line, or level restraints or hunting paterns. Using the Mythical Dane manor as a meeting place for everyone gets us all together in one place, for one purpose to meet and get to know one another. You don't have to worry about zones, you don't have to worry about mobs or Pks, tell hell, or sudden cliffs like High Hold (Which I seem to have to fall off of once a month). <br><br>I wanted to use this Thread/Story Line to get as many people's attention as I possibly could. The meeting mentioned at the crossroads is going to take place.<br><br>However I've tried on many occassions to get everyone in guild on and at a meeting several times. It never works. RL gets in the way and I end up talking to one or two peole which I can do, and do do in E-mails.<br><br>So I'm going to keep this thread alive and I want everyone to post thier ideas and thoughts on Dane. There are alot of ideas floating around, now we need to focus them. And decide what is happening and what is going to happen.<br><br>There are alot of influences to Dane from people that are no longer with us. So many times people have said that they will always be Dane. I want this to be opened to them as well.<br><br>Finally, I'm long winded, yes I know. I am a writer when I'm writing in character I turn it into a story. I think it makes things more interesting and funner to read. If not to read, at least to write. I use " ~ ~ " for emotes, and quotations for speach. Its a good way to put in observations and sparatic thoughts (which I am full of). I'm always in Character and contrary to popular belief you do not need to talk with thee's and thou's to be in character. Just talk. If you want to through actions or observations in then by all means do it. It only tells people that much more about you.<br><br>I want everyone who is or was a Dane to post here. I want every idea of what to do possible. Wynddane says we need to recruit. I completely agree, what is stopping us? Are we afraid they are going to do somthing "undanelike?" Well hell Danes have been doing that for a long time. If people screw up there will be consequences simple.<br><br>If you have absolutely no idea what to do to help Dane then I ask that you make your presence known (That mean pushing the reply button and saying /em sits down at the meeting. then push the submit button at the very least. Also read, if you only want to skim over this thread the skim it, but at least get an idea of what is being said. If this is too much to ask, then push F1 and type /guildremove<br><br>I'm tired of people being in the guild for 2 months. Never visiting the site, never talking in guild. And then making a big scene when they leave and say that no one helped them anyway. I will take 5 active members over 100 people riding the coat tails any day.<br><br>So to make a long post short (Too Late). (This would be the part you skim to if you are skimming) It is a requirement that EVERYONE post on this thread. I obviously can't remove people who are no longer with Dane, so I'm ASKING that they contribute as well. The elders must have done somthing right.<br><br>Yes I have considered Disbanding the guild. What I am now saying is TALK ME OUT OF IT. Or say your good-byes. One way or another its all going to get decided here. <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/29/01 04:39AM <br><br><br>~Desperate now having a specific task moved quickly down the road. Being an aly to the Dwarfs had its advantages. He informed the border guards of his plans to use the Crossroads as a meeting place. And the small men were quick to call for chairs and torchs food and drink. They stepped up patroles to be sure that the local hoods couldn't interfere with the meeting.~<br><br>~Desperate sat on a stump infront of the empty out turned chairs and toked on his cigar. He hoped Llue would spread the word as he had been told but he wondered. He knew bringing ex-Danes and current Danes together would bring heated conversations. Was this a wise decision? Wise or not, it was a decision. He was tired of not acting, tired of just trying to calm the seas. He was going to ride out this storm to the very end. Even if it destroyed him in the process.~<br><br>~The smoke lingered up from his pipe and encircled his head. His eye cast down to the cut on his hand. It still hurt to make a fist. How long would it be before he could duel weild. Or Swing his axe with both hands? He said the tribunal had forsaken him, and he returned the gesture. By the end of this meeting he would find out if he was alone, or if he had to make amends to his gods.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Anger destroys everything until it is all that is left <br><br> <br>      Myssi<br>Posted On 06/29/01 04:59AM <br><br><br>~ Unknown to all, the Wise Druid that first sat as Counsel to Sylverdane, Second as Leader of Dane, and finaly now sits labeled the first destroyer of Dane; sits watching her friend's pain and anguish. Of those that remain, she and she alone can understand. Myssi was tempted to speak to Desperate in Gfay, but wisdom ruled that guidance can not be given, it must be sought ...<br><br>~ A few days pass and Myssi is darting through trees to Dalnir's crypt when she senses him. Her friend, the Barbarian boy she had rescued many a time, was in Warsilk's Woods. When she finally tracks him down, as usually he is bloodied, exhausted and near death.<br><br>~ It has been a long time since the two have seen each other. They great each other like time had never passed. Desperate began talking about the current state of Dane and she stopped him.<br><br>"Desperate, I may not be a Dane. I may not be liked by many a Dane. And I may even be seen as the first Destroyer of Dane, but I have watched over Dane. I know what has become of Dane." Myssi said. Desperate smiled, he knew this would be true. "Do you seek my wisdom and thoughts on the matters as I know and remember them?"<br><br>Desperate nodded, as all great Leaders understand that knowledge is everything. "Yes. Tell me your thoughts."<br><br>Myssi paused a moment. "I do not know all the specific details of the current comings and goings of Dane so I will not comment on them. More so I have a question for you ... I hear of a coup within Dane, and not to my surprise I hear Wynddane is the instigator of this. When Sylverdane left and passed Leadership to me, Wynddane quickly verbalized is objection to this decision. In his mind, HE was the rightful successor of Sylverdane and the rightful leader. There were others that agreed I was not the right choice for Leader. But there were also many, yourself included, that understood and accepted the decision. Not wanting to deal with the internal fighting and massive rift my being leader would cause, I quickly passed leadership to you and was the first the leave the Halls of Dane after Sylverdane walked before. I remember Wynddane then opposed your leadership as well, but quickly stopped his hissy. I would hate to see Dane leave from the lands, but remember this, ALWAYS remember this ... Sylverdane the first and greatest leader of Dane did not choose his brother as his successor ... Sylverdane chose me. Why? His wisdom will come to you. I could give you the answer, but what kind of quizzical mentor would I be?"<br><br>Desperate sat there at the entrance to Dalnir's and for the first time, Myssi saw the Barbarian ... thinking ...<br><br>/ooc I came and read this at the request of more than one Dane. So, before Wynddane or anyone else for that matter gets mad at me, my presence and response was requested on this matter and it is my understanding that many old Danes responses have been requested. I TRULY do not wish to see Dane leave EQ and hope ya'll can get things worked out. I wish you all the best and have complete faith and supoort in Desperate's decision.<br><br>Wise Druid once say: I have Starfire, Drifting Death and PMS. Any questions?<br><br><br><br><br>Myssi "Mad Dog" McDoogle the Martyr of Dane<br>The Wise and Breasted One<br>Druid of the 51st Season<br>Leader of the Hammers of Vengeance <br><br>Wise Druid once say: I have Starfire, Drifting Death and PMS. Any questions?<br><br><br><br><br>Myssi "Mad Dog" McDoogle the Martyr of Dane<br>The Wise and Breasted One<br>Druid of the 51st Season<br>Leader of the Hammers of Vengeance <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 06/29/01 05:21AM <br><br><br>~Desdmona stll sits where Desperate left her. Thinking hard.It souned as tho her Father had just dismissed her. Telling her to go home.....that it isnt her problem anymore. " Stupid Man she uttered....it IS my problem. You hurt I hurt. Danes hurt I hurt." Yelling to noone " Cant you see??? Danes will always be a part of me till I die!!"<br>~ Guiltily she looks around hopeing noone heard her disrespect at calling Desperate stupid. Men sometimes are so dense.<br>~ Sitting she finishes her rum. Torn between 2 families and her love of 2 men. One her husband one her father. She wants to beat them both with a stick. Both are head strong and stubborn. Neither listen to her unles she gets really REALLY MAD!! Maybe it is MAN thing.....maybe it is a ego thing.<br>~ Words I spoke had no effect on either of them.<br>~Sighing~ What I said was right. It is the eternal struggle with in that pulls at the seams of her family.<br>~ Using her best roguely ways she silently trails after her father. Wondering what he has on his mind? Where is he going?<br>~Trembeling she stalks him. Knowing that at any moment she could bring about her own death. Faydark is instant death to her kind....the dark elves. It is a risk she will take.....for her love knows no bounds.<br>~Standing off in the distance she heard Desperate and Llue exchanging words....Men! A silly poem at a time like this.<br>But wait...... this can reveal some things I think. The words ring true. There is an air about them. Mayhaps they are right.<br>~Stepping out from the shadows she reveals her presence only for a moment.....as the guards of Butcher Block Hate her. In her shourd of stealth she lays her hand upon Desperate's shoulder. " Father I am here, I will always be here. You cant just dismiss me and sent me home. I am a part of this.....you made it so. What I said to you has some merit.....about the struggle from within. I do not claim to know it all, I am far too young. I offer you only what I have learned. What you and the other Danes have taught me. I want to be at this meeting, but I cant. I have other things that pull me home. An evil stalks the Knights and they are in imminent danger. It breaks my heart to not be here for you. Even if you dont realize it you need me. Just as I need you."<br>~ Taking a deep breath she turns to leave, taking only 3 steps before running back.<br>~ Flinging her arms around a tall Barbarian isnt easy, but she manages to do so with a leap and bound. <br>~ Embracing Desperate she wispers to him..." Father I will not be long gone. I leave you with this. An ancient magical item I was given by Hbird Truesong, Mistress of Knights Errant.<br>~Pressing into his hand a golden pendant. A talsman of faith and truth. Only the best Knights of the Heronblade possess these. Showing him her palm she reveals the brand of the Dragon Reborn burned there. I too am Knight of the Heronblade. "You must not reveal me for it will mean my death if the Forsaken learn of me. No other Dark Elf has ever been taken in as a Knight. Take this pendant, keep it close to you. It will aid you in seeing the truth in the misdt of evil. As you hold it remember your daughter, who Loves you. Also remember to seek the truth and hold to your faith. Thru it I will always be with you. I Love You. You will find the right way I am sure. Send word to me as soon as you can. I have a battle of another kind to fight now.<br>I must go."<br>~ Letting go is the hardest part, but she knows she must. For her fellow Knights are in terrable danger and they need her.<br>~ Kissing the man she adores on the cheek she turns and runs for the boat to take her to her battle.<br>~ Knowing in her heart that there are 2 battles here. One of the flesh and one of the heart.<br>~" I Love You, dear Father she wispers to the wind...... I will always be with you..........<br><br>Desdmona Shadowborn <br><br><br><br> <b