ics themselves. He hoped to find the direction with them that was not available with Dane.~<br><br>~The times were trying, and Wynddane's departure came at an ill time. Sylverdane felt betrayed. That crack grew. Sylverdane tried to hold the family and himself together, but the stress just kept building. He was hastey in decisions. Which isn't to say they were wrong, they just weren't his usual well thought out plans. When he finally decided to leave Dane, I was out hunting and couldn't be reached. The meeting that was called included only a handfull of what was then more then 200 Danes.~<br><br>"Dynomite the words that were crossed with you, came from Macdane. A young and headstrong dane with a story all his own. It was his belief that Dane should remain with Dane. That is a Dane should run it. Had your name been MyssiDane he would have accepted you no doubt." ~Desperate took a long pull from his pipe.~<br><br>~After Myssi took control of Dane, the foundation shook. And sides were instantly split. Half of the family believed that Myssi, the then ex-leader of Hammers of Vengeance was an obvious and good choice, while the rest weren't so much against her as for Sylverdane. No one would accpet that he was gone. Not even Desperate. There was nothing Desperate wanted more then to follow Sylverdane if only he would lead. But if Sylver's order was for Myssi, Desperate would follow her in his stead.~<br><br>~The split in Dane shook it hard. Another reason Desperate called Myssi Dynomite was her temper. It flared with little warning. She was quick of tongue and quicker to act. One too many crossed words flew at her and she retorted. When the smoke cleared Myssi knew she couldn't lead Dane. She had spoken with Sylverdane, and in the course of time words crossed between them, scarring thier friendship. It was decided that Fuduce would be her successor.~<br><br>~Her impatience grew as the onslaught came from members of Dane. This time it was her turn to send a /msg to