e to several victories in the war that couldn't be won.~<br><br>~It is said you are judged by the company you keep. It was proven right for two members of Dane. Who had friends with shady backgrounds. Darkenbane members. And when these sisters were getting attacked by MtS ((OOC:Sory still can't spell that guild's name)) they turned to thier friends for help. Most of the Danes were tied up in the current war with FoP, and the Sisters were unable to recieve help from thier family.~<br><br>~In less then a day rumors and accusations of a Dane, Darkenbane alliance spread. The greatest guild of good, and the worst of Evil allied? Impossible, but people are easily swayed to believe the impossible. The fact that MtS was made up of ex Family of Peace got lost in the grey lines of right and wrong. And a second war overlapped the first. Rudra's victories seemed small in comparision to the comming battles. Every Dane of age was hunted and beaten down.~<br><br>~Adaley, the heart of Dane fell in the war time and time again. And time and time again she stood up and fought. But it took more then anyone realized. The spells and blades cut her clean through to her soul and heart. The heart of Dane was pierced and shed tears on a bloodied battle field.~<br><br>"Hammers of Vengeance were just rebuilding at this point and couldn't offer thier help. Black Claws weren't organized enough. Knights Errant, Death Dealers, assistance was available from none of our allies. Swarm of Fear and Insanities Edge were at war with FoP and seemed to have a tiger by the tail. They picked thier fights carefully and avoided them otherwise. All too often Dane was left alone on the field of battle."<br><br>"Sylverdane's health was deteriorating. There were times he could barely stand up. Both guilds took advantage of Sylverdane's weakened condition. Attacking him every chance they got. Darkenbane was starting up a game. Where they were going to award points for PKing. Reign of Pain has always had a distaste for Hand of Dane, and they joined the onslaught. Dane's were butchered at every cornor. The mightiest guild in all of Norrath was standing on a wounded leg and everyone seemed to want to be the first to knock it over."<br><br>"I had taken up temperary unofficial control of Dane while Sylver recooperated. Handling the goings on, trying to save the Danes that chose to stay."<br><br>~Finally things became too much. All Sylverdane wanted was peace. That was all he ever wanted. "To be respected with out fear". Start a little casino in Norrath. Make some money, hunt with his family. He loved Dane, but when he talked about his casino that he would build, his eyes lit up. He could actually see the Roulette table, the pet fights, the poker tables~<br><br>"When the heartattack hit him, everyone was shocked. Everyone except me. It sucked the life right out of him, watching Dane go down and being powerless to stop it. I truely know how he felt. He has since forgiven Wynddane, but at the time the betrayal of his departure still stung his weakened heart. He talked to me about taking leadership of Dane. I swore to him that I would never run a guild again. And the only reason I was part of one now was because it was a family, not a guild."<br><br>"I can still remember the meeting where Sylverdane was going to step down offically as leader. I hadn't said that I would accept the position. I wanted to see the reaction. I did not want the family to be split yet again on who to follow. If Dane was going to follow me, then they were all going to follow. That was the only condition."<br><br>"It was Wynddane that nominated me as Lord Sylverdane's Successor. Salamandar seconded it, and it was unanamously voted in. I never tried to fill Sylverdane's shoes. Just his shadow. When Wynddane nominated me I was blown away. We had exchanged words several times. Our history is, a rocky one at best. And in truth I haven't forgiven him for leaving. But even with all that was between us, he believed I was the best thing for Dane. He is an unselfish man, you don't give him enough credit."<br><br>"With Wynddane seeking my replacement I know that in his heart he is doing it for Dane, not himself."<br><br>~With that Desperate rose, and bowed before Myssi.~ "Lady Myssi McDoogle, join the Danes for this meeting. You once served alongside Syvlerdane, as well as succeeded him. You are a part of Dane history, it is fitting that you be apart of our future as well."<br><br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> A Rogue's Gift <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/29/01 07:03AM <br><br><br>((OOC: When posts overlap there are always a few holes. Myssi's story took place in game, which is how I ended up in Dalnir for those that are lost ~smirks~))<br><br>~Myssi and Desperate teleported back to Bucherblock Mountains. Though weather or not she would remain for the meeting she hadn't said. While Desperate overlooked the still empty chairs he rolled his weary neck. Trying to work out the kinks that came from a long night. So much undone, so much to do.~<br><br>~Desdmona laid a hand on Desperate's shoulder. He tensed under her touch. Wishing briefly that people would stop sneaking up on him. He turned quickly and saw his daughter. Much like with Wynd, when startled his first instict was to attack. Maybe instictively he knew it was a woman's hand on his shoulder, or maybe being so tired had slowed him. But he saw the face of his Daughter before he attacked, and calmed himself quickly~<br><br>"I am here, you can't just dismiss me.." ~Desdmona had alot to say, Desperate tried to appoligize if it seemed he had turned his back on her, or told her to go away, but she was determined to get every word out. Women can be so stuborn.~<br><br>~The rogue turned to walk away befure D