him to guide him not to be his mother. I sent you to him as a child just so you might advise and also learn. Which I see you have, or you would not bear this mark upon your hand. As I said PREPARE or DIE!!"<br>~ With a start Desdmona awoke. Did I dream this or was it real? Lann Mandragon? My real father is dead, but the one she calls father still lives.<br>~Silently she begins her forms....cat on a wall, bending willow tree. As her body moved with her wepon it became clearer. What is done is done and what will be will be. I carry within me the power. The ability to pass on this honor I have learned. That is my legacy. Dane will not live or die by her hand. My adopted father will stand, I have done all I can.<br>~It is onward to battle!! The Knights of the Heronblade need her!~<br>~She winds her body to perform hawk in battle and her dagger clatters to the floor~<br>" What is happening to me," she cried!! ~Clutching her head she cries in pain as she falls to the floor.~<br>Vaguely she hears a wisper in her mind..............." I have given you one more gift. The gift of knowing."<br>~ "NOOOOO, no now I do not wish this," Desdmona cried!<br>" You have no choice the man laughed. Who do you think you are?? A mortal?? <br>~A flash exploded in her mind. It burned her nerve endings and made her skin tingle and she knew............ <br>"ONWARD TO BATTLE SHE CRIED......ONWARD TO BATTLE!!!"<br>Desdmona Shadowborn <br><br> <br>  <br><br> Brothers In Arms, Brother's at Arms <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 06/30/01 04:18AM <br><br><br>~Far from his brother's riddles, his daugher's danger and his Gods words Desperate stood in a steadily growing circle of Danes. Wynddane had returned to the circle, but to what avail. Wynddane supported Dane, this Desperate always knew, but what else was his agenda?~<br><br>"You doubt the sharpness of my wit? You doubt my convictions? What in me do you see that is unfit to stand as head of Dane?" ~Desperate's anger was steadily becoming legendary. Flashing as hot and fast as a bolt from the heavens.~ "We come here for answers, we come here for decisions as yet unmade. Dane is at a crossroad. As are we. Stand with your brothers and sisters and speak your mind."<br><br>~Wynddane remained silent. Desperate did not want this battle to be between Wynddane and himself. Atention and energy was being spent between the two and was just going to waste. Thier difference were insignificant in comparision to those that lay at the feet of the family this day. A warrior and a cleric, a human and a barbarian. The men lead completely different lives. Each with a dependance for the other in battle. But after the klank of steel, and dizzing colors of spells faded the dependency was looked at with distaste. Of needing another. It had always been so, and would always be. But Desperate wanted to lay that aside, and look upon Wynd as a man and as a brother.~<br><br>"You've called me a tyrant. You've said I act like a king. Neither of these do I see as decerning features in myself. But all too often we stand too close to our own faults to see thier truth. Mayhaps I am tyranical." ~Desperate chuckled softly~ "Just maybe I'm even a little crazy."<br><br>~Desperate turned to the Danes. Turning his head slowly, looking each in the eye. Breathing with his brother's and sisters. The same air, the same fear. The Tribunal once stood as his gods and his judges. But now his judges were his family.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Min
