 was appearent to his keen wolf awareness of it's members? Nay! Not one of these things was the most important. It was the feeling of it all as a whole. Along with the vast respect that so many travelers he came apon had for Hand of Dane. This was not "just" a guild. It was an idea that spread it's self across the lands of the world. The very strength of the guild was it's legend. A guild strong of character, a guild that was based on the efforts of many for one common goal. After meeting serveral members of this family and traveling with them while hunting and merry making and sleeping with them at their campfire, he knew that this would be his family if he could prove to them his worthyness. Now after what seems like only fleeting seconds many fear that the family is falling apart.<br><br>Agresser casts a spell and prepares to make the long journey to the halls of Dane. He knows all to well of his part in this. He knows that he must make his leader understand that what he had is not lost. That the family he is a part of is still strong, for the light shines bright as ever across the lands in the words of travelers and in the actions of Danes themselves. We can't undo what is not undone, we can strive to continue making each day yet another day's greatness for our family. To make sure our actions and deeds pass from the words of all whom we come across. The truth is that one Dane or one thousand Danes will still shine as bright on the land if their deeds and actions are talked about at the campfires of those we come across on our journeys.<br><br>Agresser Wolfheart<br>Proud member of <br>Hand of Dane<br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> Reesey was half asleep when she had an erie feeling she was being watched. <br><br> <br>      Ilaenu<br>Posted On 07/06/01 07:37AM <br><br><br>She let a few moments go bye, thinking it was only her nerves recovering from the long and drawn out day. The warrior's "feeling" then changed to "knowing" that she was being watched.<br>"Show yourself magic user," warned Reesey as she sprung from her bedding. <br>A laughter came from the shadows, "Sister, you never cease to amaze me." Ilaenu appeared out of nowhere.<br>A smile came to the beaten warrior's face, "Tis good to see you sister, it's been a long time."<br>"Aye, it has," replied Ilaenu<br>"You fly no flags now?"<br>A distant look came across Ilaenu's face as she muttered, "No, Once again I have no home."<br>"Care to talk to about it?"<br>Ilaenu answered, "I'd rather not."<br>"I'm sure Desperate would welcome you back to Hand of Dane, if you asked," said Reesey.<br>"I'm waiting for something to happen...I have this feeling that someone from our past is about to..." Ilaenu trailed off. <br><br> Ilaenu Tru'Hael <br>51st Enchantress <br>p0rn st4rRallos Zek <br> <br>  <br><br> RE: hidden in shadows nearby... <br><br> <br>      Ilaenu<br>Posted On 07/06/01 07:58AM <br><br><br>She started rubbing her temples, she was surrounded by conversations and they were giving her a headache Not to mention she was highly annoyed with the arguing between the big boobied halfling and Wyndane. Just then, Reesey got a nervous twitch and she looked around. "Hmm..," she thought to herself. Her gaze scanned the neighboring trees, she knew someone was watching...but she couldn't pinpoint where the watcher was hidden. She leaned forward and whispered in Desperate's ear, "M'lord, I have that twitch all of a sudden."<br>"Aye Darlin, I've just picked up on one myself." (OOC: I don't do a good Desperate =p)<br>"Let's be wary."<br>The barbarian nodded as his eyes continued to search the nearby forest. <br><br><br> Ilaenu Tru'Hael <br>51st Enchantress <br>p0rn st4rRallos Zek <br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      Wynddane<br>Posted On 07/06/01 09:41AM <br><br><br>:::Wynddane sits at his place at the table still being silent....only drinking and looking around at all his brothers and sister...even those he knew were there but he could not see....that's when he heard it....a voice...it spoke::<br><br>"Wynddane...."<br><br><br>:::He looked up almost mezmerized....it came again:::<br><br><br>"Wynddane....what has happened to you?"<br><br>: This time the voice startled him...he saw noone but heard a voice...he was thinking he knew this was not topasere...he got up from the table:::<br><br>Desperate said "Wynd where are you going"<br><br>:::Wynd didn't answer just looked and walked off to a clearing. He seemed to be talking to someone but noone could see who...not even with their see invis up...The danes gathered around him....trying to shake wynd out of this trancelike shape. Desperate finally grabbed him and Shook Wynd violently yelling:::<br><br>"Wynd!!!"<br><br>::As Desperate said that a Bright White light came from the Norrath Sky hitting Wynddane in the chest and almost knocking the Slayer of Vox on his back lifting Wynd off the gropund and spinning him in the air:::<br><br>Grimance and Stonelor yell at once " WYNDDANE!"<br><br>::Wynd falls to the floor on his back exhausted...Desperate makes his way to him and helps the tired Cleric up on his strong shoulders:::<br><br>Desperate says " Brother what happened?"<br><br>Wynddane mutters "A quest?"<br><br><br>Wynddane Soulcleanser<br>Cleric of Marr<br>45th Season<br><br><br>Wynddane Soulcleanser<br>Cleric of Marr<br>45th season <br><br><br><br>Message Edited on 07/06/01 10:17AM by Wynddane  <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br>User Options:  Edit Message <br> <br>      Druuni<br>Posted On 07/07/01 04:27AM <br><br><br>Ruff ruff!!!<br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 07/08/01 04:45AM <br><br><br>((OOC:))Sorry I haven't been here for 2 days, but my computer has been acting all crazy. I think it suffers from PMS. I can't load the dane web page, (if you're having a similar difficulty go to <a href="http://w