Awakening <br><br> <br>      RudraWhiteknght<br>Posted On 07/08/01 09:05PM <br><br><br>~ A soft strand of smoke, travels across a small farmstead, as a boy tends the sheep, leading them to a far field... ~<br><br>"That smells of...", Kao's voice cracking in fear.<br><br>Kao darted for the stables, leaping upon Cortez, and set out as fast as he could, for the Cavern of the Dead.<br><br>"I know I'll find you father.." Kao spoke as his horse galloped off into the mists.<br><br>-=The Awakening=- <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Crossroads <br><br> <br>      follosekker<br>Posted On 07/09/01 01:33AM <br><br><br>OOC: Please dont let any typos etc in my posting take u off the topic. I didnt have a spell checker available when I wrote this.<br><br>In the druid circle a body materializes. The old druid Follo seems content to what he sees  familiar trees, grass and hills. At his 52 season he has just returned from the largest and most mindblowing experience of his life. But as he materializes the knowledge he just thought he had, somehow seems to slip away. The only thought he seems to be able to hold on to, the only thought that somehow seems related to the journey he just finished is: This is not the only existence there is  there are others. And spirits can travel between them.<br>I must try to teach my knowledge to my fellow Danes. My dear brother and sisters.<br><br>He starts running in the direction of crossroads on his way to Kaladim, not knowing the large meeting taking place there at just this moment.<br><br>Closing in he sees there is a large gathering there, and suddenly sees old familiar faces and several new ones. He even sees faces not seen for a long time.<br><br>Hail Danes Follo says in a normal voice. Not everyone hears his salute, but as Desperate turns and hails Follo with a smile, he is greeted by all his family.<br><br>After a short introduction to the background for this meeting Follo is able to see that Desperate has been thru a hard trial. He also notices that his old friend Wynddane seems worn somehow.<br><br>Feeling that its expected he says something, Follo steps into the middel of the circle, seems to be thinking for a short while then starts speaking:<br><br>"Dear family  see around u, what do you see? Brothers and sisters from both the present and from times past.<br>Some of you spend your time thinking about the past, some of you spend your time planning the future, I say: First and foremost spend your time enjoying the present. Its here and now you can act! Its now you can make friends. Its now u can help others and gain glory. Its now you can feel joy or pain."<br><br>Glugg, glugg. Follo drinks from his bottle to clear his voice.<br><br>"Remeber our gods have mercy on us. When we die, we come alive again. My only concern is that of beeing robbed when dead. Makes me mad! Cause I have never partisipated in those acts, except when it comes to killing scum that have troubled me or my friends in the past."<br><br>Follo takes a break, hugging a small tree nearby. Then he continues:<br><br>"So there is actually no reason why we should not just be a happy family.<br>I support Desperate, and I enjoy my friendship with Wynddane and Druuni. I thank Myssi for the good advices conserning me going to Burning Woods for Hornet hunting. Lets enjoy!"<br><br>Follo feels he have spoken too long. So he concludes:<br><br>"And of cause we must recruit. There are several very nice people out there. Lets consentrate on the unguilded. We dont like when our brothers and sisters leave us to join another guild. So we must expect the same feelings arise in other guilds too, If we sort of steal their members.<br>But if we consentrate on the unguilded, we wont generate such problems."<br><br>Follo steps back and sits down.<br><br>Suddenly a Bright White light came from the Norrath Sky hitting Wynddane in the chest and almost knocking the Slayer of Vox on his back. Supported by Desperate he mutters something about a quest.<br><br>Hmm, whats this Follo thinks. <br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      RudraWhiteknght<br>Posted On 07/09/01 03:27AM <br><br><br>~Kao's horse, exhausted from hours of a feverish pace, stumbles to the ground, unable to move any longer. Springing off the fallen steed, Kao takes great strides, that would remind any folk of his Elven lineage, up the well worn pathway. His every footstep striking lightning like energy through his spine.~<br><br>"Where is that .." Kao mummured.<br><br>His stride slowed, as the brown moss clung to his father's old boots, and he came to a stop upon a lush green hill. Gazing as far as he could, he spotted the mound. It would appear quite common to most peoples that travel in these parts... just a weathered hill in a valley of many.. but Kao knew better than most people. In a circle of stones stood a pillar of Valorium, hidden from all but the truest of heart.<br><br>Kao quickly ran towards the hill, as if all of hell's furies were at his heels. He reached the green hill, and caught himself on a moss covered rock. Crawling towards the Valorium pillar, Kao uttered the prayer taught to him by this mother. He clutched his medallion... and for a moment, all things in the world fell silent.<br><br>A sharp wind blew from the Eastern mountains.. "A storm, or.." wondered Kao. He quickly made a camp before his exhaustion got the better of him. Kao laid his head down upon the soft ground, and glanced over his shoulder at the Valorium pillar, and the mountains to the East, ever blowings winds colder than Halas itself.<br><br><br><br>-=The Awakening=- <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      RudraWhiteknght<br>Posted On 07/09/01 03:46AM <br><br><br>~The lingering embers in the hearth in the Great Hall of Dane burn slowly while Desperate, Leader of Dane, sleeps deeply in a heavy sweat.<br><br>A distant thunderclap awakens him from his nightmare in a startle, as his grabs for his sword, only then realizing it was all a dream. The winds of Halas blow open the great wooden doors to his hall, while the outside guards hastily try to keep them closed. Picking his massive frame off of his throne, Desperate slides over to the doors, extending his tree trunk arms, and slamming the open doors shut.<br><br>"That should be the end of tha.." muttered Desperate before his senses perked. Something was wrong, he could smell it.<br><br>Staring across the great hall, the fire in the great hearth was burning like the furnaces of Solusek itself.<br><br>"What magic this be?!" rumbled Desperate.<br><br>Unblinkly, Desperate stared in disbelief as a great frame rose out of the long burned ashes, taking shape. He could hardly control himself. With a tremendous thunderclap, not likely to ever be heard again, the frame flew across the great hall, and smashed itself into the think stone walls of the fortress.<br><br>Rubbing his eyes in disbelief, Desperate slowly stumbled over to the wall, avoiding the flames slowing dying out on his floor. Staring up at the new portrait on his wall, he soon recognized the once discarded and long hung painting risen from the ashes...<br><br>He promptly fainted.<br><br><br><br>-=The Awakening=-<br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> FALLING <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 07/11/01 10:01AM <br><br><br>~The bickering between Dynomite and Wynddane started to make Desperate's head spin. The crowd seemed larger then it had. Desperate felt surrounded. So many faces, so many voices. Always more to do, can't stop. Desperate's mind was weary, his head was splitting.~<br><br>~A scream~<br><br>~Desperate shook his head as it felt it split in two. Looking for the source of the scream. Lluedane fell towards the ground like a meteor from the sky. He howled as he hit the ground. Desperate raises his hands trying to quiet the world and slow it down for a moment. Somthing seemed wrong. He flashed back on his last visit to the tribunal's court, and judgement. Impending doom from the heavens. Falling down fast.~<br><br>~Desperate shook his head, shaking off the weariness and sence of impending doom. Nothing was falling. Nothing was wrong or different with the world. A wolf growled, at Wynd and Myssi, then turned at snapped at thin air. Desperate heard his brother's gasp. Though more out of shock then pain.~<br><br>~To comotion going on around him seemed to have everyone's attention as well. He could neither focus on anyone, nor look away. His mind spun again. Falling disaster, things to come, things to change. Desperate shook his head again.~ "Nothing's falling." ~No one appeared to hear him. His hand still rested on Grimace's shoulder. The paladin hadn't responded. Apparently sencing the change in Desperate's mood more then anyone.~<br><br>~The warrior released his friends shoulder and stepped to the table, where Xaneth handed out a few drinks. Desperate downed a bottle trying to calm his sences. He hadn't had a drink since his visit with his Daughter. One would do him good. Desperate paused. How long ago was that visit? How long had we all gathered here? Had the gods stopped time for the Danes? Stopped the world for us to decide its fate? Does Norrath belong to the wicked and greedy? Or will Dane save it? Will Dane stand or fall?~<br><br>Fall? Looking up at the sky again, it was easy for Desperate to believe that the stars looked down awaiting the decision on the fate of the world. The stars on the edge of thier seats looking down. What if one fell from its seat to get a closer look? Falling. Again Desperate shook his head. His vision swam.~<br><br>~Red, balck, red, black, red, black. Firey, burnt. Burning, charred. Falling fire. Impending destruction. Red, black, red, black, red, black.~ <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> The Darkness of Ignorance <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 07/11/01 10:04AM <br><br><br>~~Sylverdane sat on the shore of the North and South Karanas border, looking out over the river, smoking a half smoked cigar. To his right stood a camp full of bandits, who were standing very still hoping the guildleader of the Hand of Dane would not notice them. They were less afraid of him then they were of the hulking, huge earth Elemental, Kenn, hovering next to him. It was Sylver's birthday, and he was awaiting his wife Emaus, who was due to port in and take them away for a quiet romantic dinner somewhere in the Ice Lands.~~<br><br>~Again Desperate shook his head and the world swam out of focus. Was today Sylverdane's birthday? No that was earlier in the year. Why did that thought crash into his brain like a hammer? The guildleader of Hand of Dane? No Desperate was the leader, Desperate had taken the reins behind the Lord Sylver. Desperate's arm began to throb.~<br><br>~~Sylver's arm begins to throb. He pondered all the plans for Dane, especially the long awaited and never implemented Dane Casino. How he loved the roulette wheel. Spinning round...red...black...red black.... His arm goes numb. FLASH through his mind--<br><br>RED....that first time a puma took him down in East Commons, Wynd already down beside him.<br>BLACK...the first piece of black iron, a bracer, he camped for his brother Riverdane, that would earn River the name Riverdane Blackrazor.<br>Pain shoots like poison up his arm.<br>RED....The sun behind Topasere's face as it sets, a coin in Sylver's hand and a snake fang in Topas, when a business deal turned into a friendship.~~<br><br>~Desperate shook his arm, discarding the pain and throwing it to the ground like a Dead weight. Wynddane was muttering to himself, for Dane for Dane. What was he trying to say? Desperate had realized that he hadn't heard anyone's voice. The world had stopped. What was going on? Falling. In his mind's eye he saw a meteor bouncing on a roulette wheel.~<br><br>~~BLACK...A night with Emaus in front of Sol B, when he bumped into her and invited her to River's wedding.<br>Fire ripping through his veins.<br>RED...Rudra and Sylver walking away from the Aviac House in SK, dripping with the remains of the fight that afforded him level 22....<br>BLACK...the darkness right before Alexios gave him his first Ressurection...<br>RED...The color now flashing before Sylver's eyes as the heart attack hits him full force...<br>and then<br>BLACK....Black....black...~~<br><br>~Desperate scratched his chest. The pain slowing again. Throbbing inside, now calming. Maybe he was crazy. He didn't feel crazy. His thoughts and images were crisp and sharp. He just couldn't understand them. Maybe that was insanity, being the only one who doesn't know how off you are.~<br><br>~Ilaenu's mouth moved. His eyes focused. She was beautiful. Desperate nodded to what she said. What did she say? He heard her, he had understood her. But now he was blank. What just happened? What was happening. No one appeared to see his confusion. He felt outside himself. Looking around. Falling. He fought the visions and sounds, the world that strove to break free from his mind.~<br><br>~Desperate dropped his cigar as pain exploded through his torso. Ripping like the burning fires that erruped from a wizards chant. Acid from a Necromancer's tormented incantation.~<br><br>~~A cigar falls from a twisted hand.<br><br>A man fall to the floor.<br><br>Words escape his lips...."Things are...desperate"<br><br>Afterwards, after Emaus in a state found him barely alive, and had carried him off to be tended under Wynd's hand, she returned with Rudra, where Kenn stood silently, still staring out at the water.<br><br>"Did he say anything?" she asked tearfully. "What should we do with the guild while he heals?...did he say anything at all?"<br><br>Kenn stared at her passively, stonily.<br><br>She turns to go.<br><br>"Desperate". Kenn croaked.<br><br>"Desperate?" Rudra said, eyebrow raised.<br><br>"You heard him." Emaus told Rudra, preparing to port. "Sylver said 'Get Desperate'."<br>And as they port away...<br><br>...an earth elemental named Kenn smiles, chuckles, and picks up a half smoked cigar, blowing smoke over the water.~~<br><br>~Contrary to the popular belief Desperate's mind was strong. Even as he doubted it himself. The visions bestowed on him were images of the past. Desperate would have realized this had he not listened to every's doubt of his sanity. Had he himself not doubted it. He wouldn't have fought the visions but embraced them as the Shamans had taught him. But his need to stay clear headed made him doubt. His feirce desire to prove to all, including himself made him fight. Fight off the vision. His mind was straining now as he battled off the messages from the gods. The messages from time. He had been awarded the wisdom of the past.~<br><br>~Falling from the sky. Impending disaster.~ "Nothing's falling!" Desperate's shout was heard in the world of the past, and snapped him back to the present even as he understood what was being shown to him. He took his control back. The world no longer spun, the acid no longer swept through his veins. Desperate quietly cursed his ignorance. Someone wanted to tell him somthing. But he had told them to shut up. He was shown the past, but before the future could be explained, or even the present he closed his mind severing the link.~<br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> Asleep in the world <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 07/11/01 10:05AM <br><br><br>~The world seemed suddenly normal. Where had the message gone? Desperate looked up. Nothing loomed from the sky. Nothing threatened to fall, nothing tried to crush him. As in the court of the Tribunal he again stepped into the darkness. The darkness of ignorance.~<br><br>~Wynddane was muttering to himself again. Desperate couldn't make out what he was saying. His mind clear. His ears opened. Desperate watched his brother stand, dazed and turn to leave again.~<br><br>~What the hell had happend while he was lost? The message from the gods didn't seem half as important as a word from the family expaling what he had missed.~ "Wynd! Where are you going?" ~The cleric didn't hear him or ignored him. Desperate crossed through the meeting, all eyes drawn on Wynd. This trance was not normal. The gods had deemed it impossible for the enchanters to take control of a man with spells. They had changed that long ago, so why was Wynd under someone elses control? Walking in a daze? Talking to himself.~<br><br>~Desperate looked around for Topa. That damned rogue better not be disrupting things with his jokes. Desperate gripped Wynddane's shoulder.~<br><br>~RED, BLACK, RED, BLACK, RED, BLACK....~<br><br>~DOOM FROM ABOVE. FALLING.~<br><br>~Desperate picked up a residue of the vision Wynddane was seeing. The vision Desperate had fought. When severed from Desperate the link to the gods slammed into the only other man as close to Sylver as Desperate. Wynd.~<br><br>~FALLING.~<br><br>~The warning flashed again. But too late. Fire, blindingly white covered Wynd and Desperate, cutting the two apart. Sending them flying in two seperate directions.~<br><br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      fruegel<br>Posted On 07/11/01 03:20PM <br><br><br>you a nut how long did you sit here writeing that???????<br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> "Add" <br><br> <br>      SylverMetalsmyt<br>Posted On 07/11/01 10:03PM <br><br><br>Gore drips...<br><br>Flash of steel, a limb separated from its owner....<br><br>Sound to the right...<br><br>A twist, a slice up from his heels, and another body sliced in two.....steel through flesh like a knife through butter...<br><br>--5 months in this hellhole...5 bloody stinking months with no sign of light, just an occasional food delivery made by a courier stealthy enough to get past the monkeys and get me my provisions....clerics, chanter, coming and going, aiding in the fight against Dalnir's doomed brainwashed denizens....no word from Sylver, Wynd or Fyre...did I remember to send a letter back telling them I joined in the war?-- Riverdane Blackrazor ponders the thought, as he reaches out a mailed fist and yanks a drooling coerced goblin off a terrified cleric. The goblin hits the wall and is quickly skewed like a pincushion.<br><br>All day, all night, it rages, slice hack chop, with River pausing midfight to light a cigarette and blow smoke over the feild of bodies...the stench is almost bearable now....blood, feces, sweat all mix into a perfume that is almost pleasant to the warrior. It may reek, but to him, it smelled like home.<br><br>"Here comes the next, River...." warns the current enchanter. "Mezz breaking, and it's coming in fast"<br><br>Riverdane stubs out his cigarette and spots the coerced erudite Shadowknight whipping around the corner, headed for his enchanter......the room crackle with energy, as the enchanter begins to cast.<br><br>--Gotta take that harmtouch--River thinks, as he flies forward with sword point aimed.<br><br>Through the throat of the shadowknight his blade slides, a perfect killshot, instant death. The enchanter would be impressed, had he not seen River pull that off before countless times in this never ending war.<br><br>Suddenly, the chanter watches in puzzlement, as River is jolted rigid, wideeyed....the warriors body seems ridden with electricity.<br><br>But the shadowknight was dead....the harmtouch should have died with it...<br><br>River lit up with an errie white light, blood trickling from the corner of his mouth when he bit his tongue. The chanter stepped back a pace, he didn't like the wild look in the warriors eyes...it bordered on madness.<br><br>As quickly as it had struck, the energy in the warriors limbs snapped out like a light, and his body dropped to the ground like a lifeless puppet. The chanter approached warily. Riverdane did not move.<br><br>Suddenly, with reflexes faster than the enchanter had ever seen on a man, River whipped out his hand and gripped the man's arm in a bonecrushing grip....he was pulled forward to the warrior, quite against his will, but River's grip was not to be compromised.<br><br>"What, Dane? What??" The chanter almost screamed, watching River try to make out a word. Had his arm been free he would have mezzed the metal clad gladiator and bolted for the zone.<br><br>Finally Riverdane was able to say a word, barely audible, but understandable.<br><br>"Quest..." <br><br> <br>  <br><br> The Battle For Her Life <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 07/12/01 01:39PM <br><br><br>~ The Knights have gathered is the bowels of hell.....Solusek. Standing in the pit hidden Desdmona looks at her fellow Knights, her new family. She looks at her palm. She is one of them now. Her brand marks her apart from mortals tho she bears no magic of her own.<br>~ She chuckles thinking not even Aerimus has this. The Brand.~<br>Call are made for final preperations. Tensing and beginning to sweat she looks around......Ippyy, Jr, Aerimus, Glo. Mistress Hbird, Sonnyboy, Elane. Where are the rest?? She wispers to Jr, " where is our support?" Jr rubs his hands together, looking nervous. " They are gonna come in from Sol A in a rear flank I am told." " Final instructions Hbird calls out! Ippy you front, Sonny you back him, Glo you and Jr heal 