 trying to tell Ness that her chest is on fire and her abdomen is in knots. Nesspar is desperately laying his healing hands on her body in all the places he hears her tell him. " I am dieing... my life force is draining from me," she screams in a final breath before unconscionsis takes her.<br>~ "Aerimus," yells Nesspar. " I cant stop her bleeding, it is comming to fast...... her heart. My God her legs!! Look at her legs!! Elaine!! A paladin we need lay hands or she will die!! I cant save her she has lost too much blood. I heal her as fast as she is dieing."<br>~ The Battle Rages On~ <br><br> <br>  <br><br> Death and Rebirth <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 07/12/01 03:04PM <br><br><br>~"Am I dead," she asks? "No you are here in my arms," a voice tells her. "I have told you the truth.... indeed you have born a son. I did not say he would live." <br>~ Desdmona wails loudly her heart burning and her soul empty.She is in her dreams again, but this time it is different. She sees her body and those around it. She has visions of a stange man someone she has never met....Silver somebody. Who is he?? Her mind drifts to the Hall. Silverdane isnt he the largest painting in the Hall of Danes?<br>~Her heart burns as tho it has been ripped from her. Vaguely she remembers the battle.~<br>" What of my Knights, are they.... are they okay?" "The battle is done Child you have won and lost. Do you understand?" Desdmona wispers," I have a child? What of this Babe?" " See now your husband mourns his son. you shall bear him no more. I will send you with this knowing.... you will live a long life, suffer not greatly but will bear many burdens. You belong to 2 peoples of 2 families. Your loyality will be tested from both. Silverdane of whom you wonder is the creator of your beloved Danes. You must honor him as he is returning. Just as your hand bears your brand of service to your Knights your heart bears the marks of your Danes. You are to serve them both. Just as 