nce before he is committed to the Gods."<br>~Desdmona continues........to noone as her voice is filled with pain and renewal...." His death can be seen as a birth of sorts. I was told Dane would be reborn. Thru him my, Son, bonds will be forged old hurts healed and a new foundation can be cast. I pray this will be so.<br>Now how soon can I travel?"<br>"Love you do not think clearly... you are distraught now," Aerimus soothed. " He is MY son too. I mourn him as you do. I feel uneasy at what you speak. To put our child in a place that isnt sacred and consecrated by the Gods......."<br>~To whit Desdmona replied. " We have 2 of the best clerics. Wyyndane and Nesspar they can consecrate the ground and his place will be open for all to see and come to in times of confusion. I WILL HAVE THIS..... OR BY GODS YOU WILL NOT HAVE ME!!!" Leave me to mourn and heal my body...... both of you. I will have no more of this!! I will be about in a day or so have my things ready to travel and ask Send if she will port us please? Now have some deciency and leave me to clean up."<br>~ Realizing she was harsh....she takes her husbands hand. Holding him back as the Cleric leaves the room. "Please understand.... Husband it has to be this way. I will bear no more children I already know. A fate that distresses me greatly. Cant his death mean something?? Not just a useless death committed in the throwes fo battle?? I have never asked you for anything. For this I ask a lot I know."<br>~Aerimus kisses Desdmona's forhead thinking to himself....how did this woman bind him so??? From the moment he touched her hand the first time he felt her. Her passion, her love and her soul. He could never deny her anything she asked. In the last few days he had watched her change... grow in some ways to a wisdom beyond her seasons. Her lithe body bear numerous scars and her hair now streaked with black. So strange and beautifull his lovely dark elf.<br>"It shall be as you asked, Des you know I cant deny you. I shall make the preparations and ask for Send. She should be here with you. You need a woman's help seeing as how your mother isnt here. Do you wish me to send word to your Father?"<br>"He already knows.....he heard my cry of anguish on the wind. But yes send word of our travels there, that there is to be a burial there at the cross roads and tell my Uncle Topa I didnt stab myself to kill the enemy. Yet I slayed them.<br><br>to be contimued..............<br><br>Desdmona Shadowborn <br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      Wynddane<br>Posted On 07/14/01 07:11AM <br><br><br>bump<br>=op <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 07/14/01 09:17AM <br><br><br>your being mean Wyynd........I was having fun<br><br><br><br><br>Des <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br>User Options:  Edit Message <br> <br>      Druuni<br>Posted On 07/14/01 02:38PM <br><br><br>!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!<br><br><br><br><br><br>Message Edited on 07/14/01 02:31PM by Druuni  <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      Multar88<br>Posted On 07/16/01 11:14AM <br><br><br>/snooore<br><br>Multar <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      DesperateMeasur<br>Posted On 07/20/01 03:45PM <br><br><br>((OOC:)) Well this thread is almost 1 month old. In one month, we've filled 4 pages. With more then 100 posts. The writing and creative skills of Danes has shown through these pages. And with thier words everyone has shown how much Dane has ment to them. The support for Dane is obvious.<br><br>But now this thread is remaining untouched. Stories unfinished. Thoughts unread. Had this thread died, but others started that would have been somthing else.<br><br>But I'm still hearing that Dane is dead, and should be disbanded. I've heard this from Danes, Ex-Danes and friends. People that have supported Dane, but still say it can't be saved.<br><br>Before Sylverdane left the guild was on a wobbly leg. Then when he departed and several of the most loyal Danes left with him that last leg was cut out from under us. For those of us that stayed behind an impossible task was put to us.<br><br>I tried to set up a new web page. But honestly it is easier to go to handofdane.com so the news, roster and other information was left unnoticed by most.<br><br>I promoted my officers to replace the ones that had left with Sylver, or just left. But to save Dane too much time, effort and energy was needed that most of them did not have to give.<br><br>I've attempted to reignight the fire that once burned for Dane time and time again. But where once we shone like the sun, now we could hide in the light of a firefly.<br><br>I say this, remember Dane is one of the Oldest guilds on Everquest. We were one of the largest with an amazing member count of over 200 in November of 2000'. One of the most active guilds, with our raids, events and parties. Everyone knew Dane, and our elders. <br><br>Whatever else you say about The Hand of Dane, say, "Thank you, because it was one hell of a ride." <br><br>Deep Thoughts From a Shallow Mind<br>--Desperate Measures<br>Guild Leader of<br>The Hand Of Dane<br><br><br><br>width="388" height="154"&gt;<br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Awakening <br><br> <br>      SylverMetalsmyt<br>Posted On 07/20/01 09:51PM <br><br><br>(ooc: I had considered coming back to play on Rallos, to rejoin the guild, the works, Desp...I left the threads open to lead into the quests, added Riverdane's history into it...some people responded admirably, jumped even further in, and I was just waiting for a little bit more to add the next part itself...but honestly, like I said, and had been warned, the reception to me coming back wasn't going to be warm, and in some cases even hostile...a lot of people forget I put two damned years into building that guild...instead i get people thinking they are cute with tales of where I've been, which hasnt really been too much of a secret, and pricks on the public board with how 'Shady" I am..=p...I mean, do they even know what Dane was about when it started?...or do they just remember the free loot at the giveaways?....quite honestly, what was starting out to be a nice step back into Rallos is just become more of the Same Old [censored]....whatever you wish to do with the guild is yours to do...you did a great job, and you got these people to love you....The Hand of Dane is no longer a Dane, since I'm such a [censored]...=p...it is yours, do with it as you will, but watch your back if you ever try to leave it, it will smack you on the ass on your way out...<br><br>I'm probably moving Sylverdane to another server...the air just isn't very warm here anymore<br><br>And for you information, friends and enemies alike, when I ran this guild, I gave you my real life....sorry I needed to take it back <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Sylver <br><br>User Options:  Edit Message <br> <br>      Druuni<br>Posted On 07/20/01 11:34PM <br><br><br>ooc: I hope you don't draw this conclusion all out of Dit's post? Ppl have been running around smiling here since the word got out you maight be appearing back here...and it makes me having a great feeling to. So, I've made you change your mind once before...only temporarily though. <br>So, this one'll be for you to decide. Anyway I would..really I mean it, LOVE to see you back even if it's only for trying things out... Your talent for making people *feel* things in this game is---extraondinary! (I recall how I was just sitting in Lake Dane, not moving at all when I kept watching tells and /gu during the Taja/Kristanna episode...and trust me, when you told us you were crying behind the keys...I think you know you were NOT alone about that...;) -And thus it really isn't strange that a lot of them backfire at you, nomatter how much right or wrong things you would do...you might have been *the* largest personality on the server, and as we all know: With fame comes blame.<br><br>Anyway: When you gave us the MAGIC in those 2 years, you gave us something neither *you* nor anyone else can take away from us again.<br><br>Dane is Dane, period!<br><br><br>(I'd love to see ya again, for sure. Wish you were'nt so STUBBORN! ...lol, do whats best for ya anyway, bro =)<br><br>/salute SylverRiverThunderrShadowHip-etc-Dane!<br><br><br>(= Druuni =) <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Sylver <br><br> <br>      SylverMetalsmyt<br>Posted On 07/20/01 11:39PM <br><br><br>sigh...<br><br>I just went rather ballistic on the public board...<br><br>...and the gut reaction I got was from not only Dit but someone within Dane itself...<br><br>I am going to take a long drag of a cigarette and chill from these boards for a little while....I thank you always Dru for your feeling/comments, you were/are a spark of light and have been ever since Dane Isle...<br><br>Right now I am running hot, and it's probably not best to be making decisions when like that...<br><br>...but damned am I furious... <br><br> <br>  <br><br> Sylver <br><br> <br>      RudraWhiteknght<br>Posted On 07/21/01 12:05AM <br><br><br>*shrug*<br><br>I'll play if you play =p<br><br><br><br>Rudra <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Sylver <br><br> <br>      Topasere<br>Posted On 07/21/01 12:30AM <br><br><br>All of us old timers just simply need to reunite in Shadowbane or horizons or something &amp; try again using what we've learned you all might also want to check out <a href="http://www.darkageofcamelot.com" target="_blank">www.darkageofcamelot.com</a> this game shows some SERIOUS roleplaying potential mainly due to its historical accuracy in dealing with the pagan religions of old europe takes place just after the fall of king Arthur <br><br>~Topasere~<br>~To steal from the rich &amp; give to the poor means to be poor &amp; steal untill you become Rich!!~<br><br>p&gt;<br><br><br><br><br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Sylver <br><br> <br>      RudraWhiteknght<br>Posted On 07/21/01 03:04PM <br><br><br>Shadowbane rewards roleplaying, they've said it straight out. Shadowbane is PvP, with a purpose, I'm not killing Darkenbane over and over with no end. It's the only game for me, check out their page, <a href="http://www.shadowbane.com" target="_blank">www.shadowbane.com</a>, they've released a lot in the last few weeks.<br><br><br><br>Rudra <br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Furry builds itself, and not much else <br><br> <br>      Soltry<br>Posted On 07/22/01 10:15AM <br><br><br>Oh My! The little Cleric wonders, yes she is new to the great Halls of Danes but, will her words carry any comfort to her angered guildleader? M'lord I feel your pain and Know it is the way of the mighty warrior to not think as quickly as swings his axe. But, Sit M'lord calm yourself there are newcomers as myself that wish to learn the ways of the founding fathers of the House of Dane. Please do not deny me the chance to lean them from you. As a new little sister a plead with you. <br>~Soltry sits quietly in hopes that the rampage will end and Des will come to his senses.~ <br><br> <br>  <br><br> Returning to the Crossroads <br><br> <br>      Desdmona<br>Posted On 07/23/01 09:59AM <br><br><br>~Desdmona and Aerimus port in to Faydark with Send Munie. The kind durid binds them both. With a smile and a sow she gives her condoleances and departs. Leaving the couple alone.~<br>~Walking slowly, even with spirit of the wolf, Aerimus and Desdmona approach the cross roads. Carrying a tiny coffin between them.~<br>~Quietly approaching the meeting, they look and listen to all who are speaking. Taking a seat they wait till it is the proper time to speak to Desperate.~<br>~ Faced with a heart wrenching task ahead of them and knowing the turmoil that Dane is in. They know it is better to wait untill they are called upon.~<br>~ Desmdona wispers in cant to Topa...."Uncle I have returned."<br><br>Desdmona Shadowborn<br><br><br>Message Edited on 07/23/01 09:53AM by Desdmona  <br>  <br><br> Continued.... <br><br> <br>      Tryzen<br>Posted On 07/26/01 07:16PM <br><br><br>Moving ever so slowly as he approached the gathering, Dujinn began to sweat. He didnt know what reaction this group would have to him suddenly appearing out of nowhere. Feeling the tension rise he finally decided to wait for another time. Backing up to his original spot and keeping an eye on that warrior lass who seemed to keep scanning the area, he crouched and gathered his shadows around him. Dujinn retreated back to the entrance of Dagnors Cauldron while he made and discarded new plans of deliverance.<br>Why is this so hard? Dujinn whispered.<br>Maybe because your weak? a voice said behind him and made his heart skip a beat.<br>Unsheathing his mace, Dujinn spun and faced his adversary who was a wizard by the looks of him.<br>What can I do for you sorcerer? Dujinn asked already knowing what the reply would be.<br>Why die of course! he replied as he started the mystical gestures for a spell.<br>Dujinn dodged that bolt that screamed at him and leapt toward his opponent swinging his mace. <br>Gasping as a magical shield deflected his mace, Dujinn stepped through the shadows to some distance away.<br>Chuckling the wizard began his next spell. Summoning all his skill and training Dujinn prepared to face the caster win or lose. Throwing up a disease cloud around the wizard he charged in mace leading.<br>The Charge shattered the casters concentration and the spell he was weaving crumbled as Dujinns mace thumped into his chest.<br>Shield or not you will die today wizard! Dujinn screamed as he pummeled the man. <br>Dujinn began to cast a spell and the wizard clutched his chest screaming in pain, interrupting a counter spell.<br>The battle lasted what seemed like forever. Mystical spells met with the force of shadows in constant conflict for hours. Sweat poured from dujinn with every counterstrike and the spells came at him slower and slower. <br><br>Sitting against the tree Dujinn examined his burns. His breathing was shallow and he was weak but smiling. Glancing at the corpse of the wizard he pulled some bandages out of his pocket. Something the wizard said during the battle troubled him. Why would that guy want to find the Danes? Dujinn pondered.<br>After bandaging up the open wounds, Dujinn hobbled over to the nearest goblin camp to finish his healing.<br><br><br>Tryzen Tru'Hael<br>55th Templar of Reverant<br>Cleric of Tunare<br><br> <br>  <br><br> RE: Continued.... <br><br>User Options:  Edit Message <br> <br>      Druuni<br>Posted On 07/28/01 02:39PM <br><br><br>~The great wolf lifts her head and gazes towards west..what was those distant sounds of battle?<br>Putting her head to rest between her paws again, she looks back towards the familys head...Desperate looks like he is in deep thoughts. What will be his next step concerning the Dane? Times of adventure are ahead...in one way or another.<br><br>*The wind strenghtens its force towards the tall treetops above the Dwarven outpost..still not touching the mixed group crouching together by the fire on the Crossroads...*<br> <br> 
<br /><br />--------------------<br />Druuni, sewing lunatic of Rallos and officer of Dane.

